39 whom shall be the owner of a veteran owned business. The Speaker shall designate a
40 legislative member of the committee as chairperson of the committee.
41 (3) Powers and duties. The committee shall undertake a study of the conditions, needs,
42 issues, and problems mentioned above or related thereto, including, but not limited to, a
43 determination of where data sets may be disaggregated by race, ethnicity, gender,
44 disability, veteran status, or other key demographic variables, and recommend any action
45 or legislation which the committee deems necessary or appropriate.
46 (4) Meetings. The chairperson shall call all meetings of the committee. The committee
47 may conduct such meetings at such places and at such times as it may deem necessary or
48 convenient to enable it to exercise fully and effectively its powers, perform its duties, and
49 accomplish the objectives and purposes of this resolution.
50 (5) Allowances, expenses, and funding.
51 (A) The legislative members of the committee shall receive the allowances provided
52 for in Code Section 28-1-8 of the Official Code of Georgia Annotated.
53 (B) Members of the committee who are state officials, other than legislative members,
54 or who are state employees shall receive no compensation for their services on the
55 committee, but they may be reimbursed for expenses incurred by them in the
56 performance of their duties as members of the committee in the same manner as they
57 are reimbursed for expenses in their capacities as state officials or employees.
58 (C) Members of the committee who are not legislators, state officials, or state
59 employees shall receive a daily expense allowance in an amount the same as that
60 specified in subsection (b) of Code Section 45-7-21 of the Official Code of Georgia
61 Annotated, as well as the mileage or transportation allowance authorized for state
62 employees.
63 (D) The allowances authorized by this resolution shall not be received by any member
64 of the committee for more than five days unless additional days are authorized. Funds
65 necessary to carry out the provisions of this resolution shall come from funds
