66 appropriated to the House of Representatives; except that funds for the reimbursement
67 of the expenses of state officials, other than legislative members, and for the
68 reimbursement of the expenses of state employees shall come from funds appropriated
69 to or otherwise available to their respective agencies.
70 (6) Report.
71 (A) In the event the committee adopts any specific findings or recommendations that
72 include suggestions for proposed legislation, the chairperson shall file a report of the
73 same prior to the date of abolishment specified in this resolution, subject to
74 subparagraph (C) of this paragraph.
75 (B) In the event the committee adopts a report that does not include suggestions for
76 proposed legislation, the chairperson shall file the report, subject to subparagraph (C)
77 of this paragraph.
78 (C) No report shall be filed unless the same has been approved prior to the date of
79 abolishment specified in this resolution by majority vote of a quorum of the committee.
80 A report so approved shall be signed by the chairperson of the committee and filed with
81 the Clerk of the House of Representatives.
82 (D) In the absence of an approved report, the chairperson may file with the Clerk of the
83 House of Representatives a copy of the minutes of the meetings of the committee in lieu
84 thereof.
85 (7) Abolishment. The committee shall stand abolished on December 1, 2025.
